The coaches are divided into urban, where there are standing seats and limited maximum speed, interurban with standing seats and higher allowed speed and long-distance coaches without standing seat with the highest allowed maximum speed and seats equipped with safety belts.
Like on the plane, says an expert.
Jaroslav Hořín, expert at BESIP (Road Traffic Safety) in transportation, does not see the displacement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"When there is regular traffic, there is no danger. The situation can be compared to that of the service in aircraft.
Nor is it sure when turbulence will occur and the hostess can beat her head."
"In the event that the coach had suddenly braked, the laws of physics would obviously be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or a tram.
The carrier must manage the safety of stewards through internal regulations," he said and also believes that from the point of view of the law, the issue is not resolved.
Jančura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only coach carrier to offer stewards services.
He hired two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not consider their profession to be a risky profession.
“But as soon as I feel like this is a risky trade, I will eliminate it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and journal at boarding.
This would also reduce the costs,” he said.
The safety concern is the reason for the absence of stewards in his vehicles by the director of the Asiana Alexey Litvine, who assures, in comparison with SA, a very small number of lines.
"We don't have hostesses. We've been opposed to it from the beginning.
Sooner or later it will end in a deadly accident," he told Týden.cz a year ago.
An immense tragedy has come
A young hostess from the Plzeň region, who had been working for the company for two years, died in the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop band without using a flash and blocked the way to the coach.
The latter's driver tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he sneaked him by his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards have been sold.
"In the case of long distance lines, it is not possible to reserve these seats, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the truck driver.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but with regard to financial compensation, it will also rely on the culprit.
A change to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment to the law, which has been being drafted for more than a year by a group of 30 experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the travel of stewards on the coach.
“It has not reached any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the point system, the maximum speed on the highway and the use of the cell phone at the wheel," says expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider stewards' activity to be a thing that would fundamentally jeopardize passenger safety," said Hanzelka, saying the control of coach safety is under the authority of the police and the Office for Occupational Safety.
