Soon, on October 8, the hearings concerning the ongoing criminal proceedings against János Zuschlag and his accomplices will begin.
The politician and his accomplices are accused of continuous and regular criminal organization scams, resulting in particularly serious harm, and other charges have been held against them, such as forgery and use of forgery.
According to the prosecution, the money from grants was spent for personal purposes, while the benefits were justified by false invoices.
The money of the state and municipalities, about 65 million HUF in total, went on the one hand into the cashiers of the Fiatal Baloldal movement and on the other hand into the pockets of some people.
