From now on, a maximum of half of 700 billion can be spent. The first 250 billion will be issued immediately after the bill is passed by Congress, probably Monday. This first amount will be used to the Treasury Secretary to purchase dubious debts from banks, while the use of the additional 100 billion dollars will be left at the President's discretion.
